@model KyoS.Web.Models.TCMIntakeMiniMentalViewModel

<div class="col-md-push-12">
    <div class="form-group col-md-4">
        <label asp-for="TcmClient.Client.Name" class="control-label">Name of Recipient</label>
        <input asp-for="TcmClient.Client.Name" class="form-control" readonly>
        <span asp-validation-for="TcmClient.Client.Name" class="text-danger"></span>
    </div>
    <div class="form-group col-md-2">
        <label asp-for="TcmClient.CaseNumber" class="control-label">Case No.</label>
        <input asp-for="TcmClient.CaseNumber" class="form-control" readonly>
        <span asp-validation-for="TcmClient.CaseNumber" class="text-danger"></span>
    </div>
    <div class="form-group col-md-3">
        <label asp-for="Date" class="control-label"></label>
        <input asp-for="Date" class="form-control" readonly>
        <span asp-validation-for="Date" class="text-danger"></span>
    </div>
    <div class="form-group col-md-3">
        <label asp-for="TcmClient.Casemanager.Name" class="control-label">Examiner Name</label>
        <input asp-for="TcmClient.Casemanager.Name" class="form-control" readonly>
        <span asp-validation-for="TcmClient.Casemanager.Name" class="text-danger"></span>
    </div>

</div>
<div class="form-group col-md-12">
    <pre>
        The Mini Mental State Examination (MMSE) is a tool that can be used to systematically and thoroughly assess mental 
        status. It is an 11-question measure that tests five areas of cognitive function: orientation, registration, attention and 
        calculation, recall, and language. The maximum score is 30. A score of 23 or lower is indicative of cognitive impairment

        Maximum         Score 
                                     <strong>Orientation</strong>
           5         <input asp-for="OrientationWhat" style="width:5%">    What is the (year) (season) (date) (day) (month)?
           5         <input asp-for="OrientationWhere" style="width:5%">    Where are we (state) (country) (town) (hospital) (home) (office) (floor)?

                                     <strong>Registration</strong>
           3         <input asp-for="RegistrationName"  style="width:5%">    Name 3 objects: 1 second to say each. Then ask the patient
                                     all 3 after you have said them. Give 1 point for each correct answer. 
                                     Then repeat them until he/she learns all 3. Count trials and record     
                                     Trials  <input asp-for="Trials" style="width:5%">
                                     <strong>Attention and Calculation</strong>         
           5         <input asp-for="Attention" style="width:5%">    Serial 7’s. 1 point for each correct answer. Stop after 5 answers.
                                     Alternatively spell “world” backward. Give 1 point for each letter spelled correctly.

                                     <strong>Recall</strong>
           3         <input asp-for="Recall" style="width:5%">    Ask for the 3 objects repeated above. Give 1 point for each correct answer.

                                     <strong>Language</strong>
           2         <input asp-for="LanguageName" style="width:5%">    Name a pencil and watch.
           1         <input asp-for="LanguageRepeat" style="width:5%">    Repeat the following: “No ifs, ands, or buts”
           3         <input asp-for="LanguageFollow" style="width:5%">    Follow a 3-stage command: “Take a paper in your hand, fold it in half, and 
                                     put it on the floor.”
           1         <input asp-for="LanguageRead" style="width:5%">    Read and obey the following: "Close your eyes"
           1         <input asp-for="LanguageWrite" style="width:5%">    Write a sentence.
           1         <input asp-for="LanguageCopy" style="width:5%">    Copy the design shown:

                     <input asp-for="LanguageCopy" style="width:5%">   <strong>Total Score</strong>
    </pre>
</div>
